        <fileDesc>
            <titleStmt>
                <title>Translation of 尹文子 into (English)</title>
                <editor role="translator">Christooph Harbsmeier</editor>
            </titleStmt>
            <publicationStmt>
                <p>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org<seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-7a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T20:42:39.441+09:00">the true gentleman will not exercise that ability.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-7a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T20:46:30.797+09:00">It is not as if the true gentleman takes pleasure in speaking up</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T21:54:17.277+09:00">As for names, they are what properly sorts out shapes.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T21:55:09.893+09:00">If the sorting out of shapes comes from names</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T21:55:35.423+09:00">then names must not deviate form the norm.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:30:25.33+09:00">If one governs in accordance with the Supreme Way</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:12:08.092+09:00">then disputers, legalists, Confucians, Mohists disappear of themselves;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:13:29.825+09:00">and if one governs in accordance with disputers, legalists, Confucians, and Mohists</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:18:41.104+09:00">then one still has no chance of getting away from the Way.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:27:50.449+09:00">it is the treasure of the good,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:32:58.863+09:00">Those who govern in accordance with the Way</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:39:27.662+09:00">their names and their lot in life become more distant from each other every day.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-17a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-12T21:31:55.521+09:00">直解：29:人君承接萬物，必劃分而區別之。使之各安其分。</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-17a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-12T22:02:31.805+09:00">they all tried to draw it and gave up half way through.</seg>
                </p>
